	LinkedInV-Card







John A. Scully

 John is a founding shareholder of Cooper & Scully. A highly skilled and experienced trial lawyer, John's hallmark is his dedication to client satisfaction.

 John is board certified in both Civil Trial Law and Personal Injury Trial Law by the Texas Board of Legal Specialization. In addition, John is Board Certified by the American Board of Professional Liability Attorneys. He has been elected to the American Board of Trial Advocates (ABOTA), and was recognized from 2009-2010 by the legal directory Chambers USA - America's Leading Lawyers for Business.

 According to Chambers USA, John is "'sharp-witted with a great track record nationwide.'" Chambers further found that "clients hail him as 'an amazing litigator' whose courtroom skill manifests itself as 'brilliance at work.' 'Extremely keen-minded and creative.'" Chambers also found that John is "an outstanding practitioner whom you can rely on to achieve good results, even in the trickiest of cases. Praised as 'a clued-up guy who is always able to assess a situation and choose the best way to resolve matters."

 John has been selected to D Magazine’s Best Lawyers in Dallas (2015-2017). John is AV Preeminent Peer Review rated by Martindale-Hubbell and has been featured in the Texas Super Lawyers® list by Thomson Reuters Legal from 2003-2016.

 John is routinely retained to try high-dollar exposure cases in the areas of business litigation, catastrophic injury and wrongful death and professional liability. His professional liability practice includes representation of hospitals and other health care providers, attorneys, law firms and other professionals. John has served as national trial counsel on birth and catastrophic injury litigation for numerous hospital systems and insurance carriers, and as national coordinating counsel for one of the nation’s largest health care organizations.

 Over the past 30 years, John has developed a diverse civil trial practice involving an array of industries, including health care, insurance, real estate, construction, oil and gas, financial and pharmaceuticals. He has represented a variety of clients ranging from Fortune 500 companies to governmental entities in complex commercial litigation, personal injury lawsuits, class actions, administrative proceedings and investigations. John has tried and managed lawsuits in state and federal courts throughout Texas and numerous other states.

 John and his wife, Karen, have three children.  While John has always been a sports fanatic, his support of his children's activities led to his passionate involvement in coaching youth sports. John served as head football coach of the Parish Episcopal 7th/8th grade team for many years, and as assistant football coach of the school's high school team since 2009. John also serves on Parish's Board of Trustees and served as Chair of the Board of Visitors for his undergraduate alma mater DePauw University.

  

